The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 June is 42,547 (4,924.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 June, there were 211 new confirmed cases (24.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 May, there were 91 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 132% (120 extra cases).
